@NODE HowToStart "How to start the program"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}Start from a shell:@{ub}
   
   [Run] @{b}LoginTasks@{ub}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "WhatIsIt" "What is it for?"

@{fg shine}What does the program?@{fg text}

   This program is for user of the @{"MultiUser-FileSystem" link "muFS" 0}.
   It  allows  the login to one (or more) task(s), if you have the required
   rights to access them;-)

   Because @{b}@{fg shine}LoginTasks@{ub}@{fg text} uses @{"MUI" link "MUI" 0}, it has @{"a comfortable and nice GUI" link "/LoginTasks.gif/Main" 0};-)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "muFS" "MultiUserFileSystem"

   @{b}@{i}@{fg highlight}What is muFS?@{ub}@{ui}@{fg text}

   @{fg highlight}muFS@{fg text} is the abbreviation of @{b}M@{ub}ulti-@{b}U@{ub}ser-@{b}F@{ub}ileSystem.
   It is programmed by Geert Uytterhoeven for the Commodore Amiga Computer.
   It  requires  AmigaOS  2.0  and  above  and  is  written as a normal DOS
   FileSystem, so that it should work together with nearly all programs.

   Who wants to know more about @{fg highlight}muFS@{fg text} should read the 'MultiUser.doc', which
   is enclosed the @{fg highlight}muFS-Packet@{fg text}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "MUI" "MagicUserInterface"
@{LINDENT 3}
                          This application uses


                        MUI - MagicUserInterface

                (c) Copyright 1993/94 by Stefan Stuntz


MUI  is  a system to generate and maintain graphical user interfaces.  With
the  aid  of  a  preferences  program,  the  user of an application has the
ability to customize the outfit according to his personal taste.

MUI  is  distributed as shareware.  To obtain a complete package containing
lots  of examples and more information about registration please look for a
file  called  "muiXXusr.lha"  (XX  means the latest version number) on your
local bulletin boards or on public domain disks.

          If you want to register directly, feel free to send


                         DM 30.-  or  US$ 20.-

                                  to

                             Stefan Stuntz
                        Eduard-Spranger-Stra▀e 7
                             80935 M№nchen
                                GERMANY
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements for LoginTasks"

@{b}@{u}@{fg fill}Requirements:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  There are some requirements which have to be fulfilled, before you
  can use @{b}@{fg shine}LoginTasks@{ub}@{fg text}:

   @{b}@{fg fill}*@{ub}@{fg text} of course you need @{"muFS" link "muFS" 0} (Multi-User-FileSystem by Geert
     Uytterhoeven;-)

   @{b}@{fg fill}*@{ub}@{fg text} AmigaOS 2.0+
     As of AmigaOS v2.1 @{b}@{fg shine}LoginTasks@{ub}@{fg text} could be localizised to your preferred language
     (german and english are enclosed)

   @{b}@{fg fill}*@{ub}@{fg text} and of course @{"MUI" link "MUI" 0}, I didn't know exactly which version you need atleast,
     but it is allways the best, if you get the newest version
     (@{b}@{fg shine}LoginTasks@{ub}@{fg text} is developed with v2.2)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "History" "History of LoginTasks"

@{b}@{u}@{fg fill}History:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Version 1.0:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}
   @{fg shine}37.9 (01.12.94):@{fg text} 
        ╖ Online Help added

   @{fg shine}37.8 (27.11.94):@{fg text} 
        ╖ doubleclick -> Login
        ╖ More Hotkeys
        ╖ Localizised!

   @{fg shine}37.7 (31.07.94):@{fg text}
        ╖ Login() works now with mui.mListNextSelected.
        ╖ If a login to 'This User' failed, the current user will be used!
        ╖ small bug fixes

   @{fg shine}37.6 (30.07.94):@{fg text}
        ╖ Login failed with the active entry (no multiselect)!
        ╖ During the login the program will 'sleep'.
        ╖ CycleChain changed, PopThisUser was ignored.

   @{fg shine}37.5 (26.05.94):@{fg text}
        ╖ The Task-ListView will be refreshed only after the task-list is loaded!

   @{fg shine}37.4 (09.04.94):@{fg text}
        ╖ If you login to more than one task, the password-request will appear only once!

   @{fg shine}37.3 (07.04.94):@{fg text}
        ╖ A Select-PopUp added to select entries!

   @{fg shine}37.2 (04.04.94):@{fg text}
        ╖ The Listview now is a MultiSelect-ListView!

   @{fg shine}37.1 (01.04.94):@{fg text}
        ╖ Now it works like it should!

   @{fg shine}37.0 (21.03.94):@{fg text}
        ╖ First version, only the GUI created -> Probs with MuiMakros;-(
@ENDNODE

