@ENDNODE

@NODE "Filter" "User-Filter"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}User-Filter:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  This string gadget holds the user id, which should be filtered out.
  Only tasks with this id will be shown!

  You can use AmigaDOS-Patterns here!

  The gadget next to this opens a listview, where you can select
  a user.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Select" "User-Select"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}User-Select:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  This string gadget holds the user id, which tasks should be selected.

  You can use AmigaDOS-Patterns here also!

  The gadget next to this opens a listview, where you can select
  a user.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Status" "The Status-Line"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Status-Line:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  This space shows how many tasks are selected.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "UpdateTasks" "Update Listview"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Update Listview:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  If you press this gadget, the tasks will be reread and @{"filtered" link "Filter" 0}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Login" "Login to a Task"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Login to a Task:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  This gadget changes the owner of the @{"selected" link "Select" 0} task(s).
  The user ID of the @{"selected" link "Select" 0} task(s) will be changed to the user which is
  entered in the @{"to-" link "LoginTo" 0}stringgadget, if he is able to!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "LoginTo" "New Owner of the Task(s)"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}New Owner of the Task(s):@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  You have to enter here the user ID, which should @{"login" link "Login" 0} to the
  @{"selected" link "Select" 0} task(s). 

  The gadget next to this opens a listview, where you can select
  a user.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Yourself" "Your UserID"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Your UserID:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  Here you have to enter your UserID.

  Thats usefull, if you want to @{"login" link "Login" 0} to multiple tasks!

  The gadget next to this opens a listview, where you can select
  a user.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Hide" "Hide Window"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Hide Window:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  This closes the window, but @{fg shine}DIDN'T@{fg text} @{"quits" link "Quit" 0} the program.
  It can be revealed with a defineable key in @{fg fill}MUI-Prefs@{fg text}, or
  with the program @{fg fill}ExChange@{fg text}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Save" "Save MUI-Settings"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Save MUI-Settings:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  This is for saving the size and position of the window, so the
  window opens at the same position with the same size after a reboot.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Use" "Use MUI-Settings"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Use MUI-Settings:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  This is for using the size and position of the window only till a reboot.
  Or if you have your ENV: in a resetproof RamDisk (like me;-), till a cold
  reboot!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Quit" "Quit LoginTasks"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Quit LoginTasks:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  This is for quitting @{b}@{fg shine}LoginTasks@{ub}@{fg text}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "TaskName" "Task Name"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Task Name:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  Name of the task.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "TaskOwner" "TaskOwner"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Task Owner:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  Owner of the task.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "TaskType" "TaskType"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}TaskType:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  Type of the task.
  
  It will be @{fg fill}CLI <number>@{fg text}, @{fg fill}Task@{fg text}, @{fg fill}Process@{fg text} or @{fg fill}hmm?@{fg text}.
  @{fg fill}hmm?@{fg text} shouldn't occur, but if its occur contact @{"me" link "Author" 0}!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "TaskPri" "TaskPriority"

@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}TaskPriority:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

  The priority of the task.
@ENDNODE
